<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-17 01:37 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6579 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-BARKLEY-HNS &LR;      01-17 0570
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-BARKLEY-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
Barkley likes Rockets plus star
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; By MICHAEL MURPHY &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; c. 1998, Houston Chronicle &LR;  &QL; 
Free agent Charles Barkley said Saturday that the Rockets remained
his first choice as the team for which to play _ if Houston lands a
free agent who will help it win this season.
</P>
<P>
   Scottie Pippen and Antonio McDyess, two of the highest-profile
free agents on the market, are said to be considering signing with
the Rockets. And should one do so, Barkley said he wouldn't be far
behind.
</P>
<P>
   ``Houston is No. 1 in my heart,'' said Barkley, who is in Las
Vegas for the Mike Tyson fight. ``Houston is still No. 1, and they
will always be No. 1. But I think they're handicapped right now.
They have to sign Antonio McDyess or Scottie Pippen.
</P>
<P>
   ``Right now I'm just hanging back, seeing what happens. If I
leave Houston, then I'm going to meet with the stars on every team
(with which he's considering signing). I want to see what their
thinking is and what their goals are for the season. All good free
agents shop around, don't they?''
</P>
<P>
   And several teams have Barkley on their shopping lists. The
rumor mill had Barkley visiting New York this weekend, but Barkley
said he had no plans to meet with the Knicks.
</P>
<P>
   Instead, the Seattle SuperSonics appear to have the inside track
should Barkley decide against re-signing with the Rockets.
</P>
<P>
   Paul Westphal, Barkley's former coach in Phoenix, took over the
Sonics this season, and joining Barkley in Las Vegas were Seattle
stars Vin Baker and Gary Payton.
</P>
<P>
   ``New York is interesting to me,'' Barkley said, ``They called,
but I told them that while I'm interested, I'm not going to talk
just yet. I think I'm going to wait and see what everyone does (in
the free-agent market). Maybe we'll talk next week.
</P>
<P>
   ``But I'd say that right now, Seattle is very interesting to me.
Paul Westphal is one (reason), but Seattle is a darned good team _
they have very good players there. I could see myself fitting in
there.''
</P>
<P>
   Especially because Barkley said he didn't care what role he
played with the Sonics, or how much money he's paid.
</P>
<P>
   After recovering from offseason surgeries to repair a double
hernia and a torn right triceps tendon, Barkley said he just wants
to go someplace where he could help a team win.
</P>
<P>
   ``I could start, or I could be the sixth man, whatever,'' he
said. ``I really don't care. I just want to be a contributor on a
winning team.
</P>
<P>
   ``The money? I don't care about that, either. I'd play for one
of the (salary-cap) exceptions _ whatever. I just want to go to a
good team, and Seattle looks like a really good team. They have a
lot of talent.''
</P>
<P>
   But Barkley, 35, said he wouldn't call his Las Vegas jaunt a
recruiting trip for the Sonics.
</P>
<P>
   ``A recruiting trip, is that what you'd call it?,'' said Barkley
of his time with Payton and Baker. ``No, this is more just good
friends who want to meet face-to-face.''
</P>
<P>
   But the Rockets remain No. 1 _ if they get a player such as
Pippen.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll tell you what, should they sign Pippen, that would change
my whole realm of thinking,'' Barkley said. ``But I don't think I'm
going to talk to anybody just yet. Like I said, I'm going to stay
out and see what happens. As for the Rockets, I really believe that
Scottie Pippen and Antonio McDyess are holding all the cards right
now. Let's see how they play them.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
