Dress up a 340-pound bearded mechanic in silk sheets, put Arafat
headgear and sunglasses on a couple of employees, hire two hookers
as harem girls and strip the logos off your own private plane.
That's what witnesses say jeweler Jack Hasson did to fool Detroit
broadcasting tycoon Aben Johnson into thinking he was meeting with
``Prince Akhmed,'' nephew of the Sultan of Brunei, at Palm Beach
International Airport. (McLachlin, Palm Beach Post). 40-50. MOVED
