<HEADLINE>
WELL, THAT SHOULD SEAL JERRY WEST'S DECISION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Of the current Lakers free agents who played for the team last
season _ Rick Fox, Mario Bennett, Jon Barry and Shea Seals _ who
should be re-signed in '99?
</P>
<P>
   Seals. No question.
</P>
<P>
   After all, he's far and away leading an Internet poll that's
being conducted right now _ on his own Web site.
</P>
<P>
   At the official Shea Seals cyberhome (http://www.geocities.com/
Colosseum/ Park/2596/index2.html), the guard injured for most of
last season and still rehabbing leads the voting with 45 percent
(36 of the 80 cast); Fox is second at 28 percent (22 votes).
</P>
<P>
   Something that ought to help Seals' case is that his site
provides a link to his coach's Web site (http://www.delharris.com).
Except that for the last few months, the Harris site hits an error
code and proclaims the document is not found.
</P>
<P>
   Which pretty well sums up last season.
</P>
<P>
   __ Kickball: A fantasy soccer game using teams and players from
the English Premier League has been launched by SportsLine USA.
It's called the ``Soccernet Soccer Challenge'' (
http://soccerchallenge. commissioner.com). The tournament is open
to Web users in the U.S., United Kingdom, Australia and Canada for
$19.95. There's a $2,500 grand prize as well as other season and
weekly prizes.
</P>
<P>
   (FYI: Avoid drafting Manchester United's Nicky Butt. The
midfielder has been out with a knee injury.)
</P>
<P>
   __ Once a pawn a time: The only official online chess program
sanctioned by the U.S. Chess Federation is offered as a beta
program on Kesmai's online game site (http://www.gamestorm.com),
soon to be a premium membership game on the multiplayer game site.
</P>
</TEXT>
