<P>
   NY-TRASH-VIRGINIA (New York) _ Yes, Virginia, there is a lot of
trash in New York. And getting rid of it is a problem. But where to
go? A look at why nobody in the Old Dominion wants Gotham's
garbage.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move this story by 7:45 p.m. ET in `a' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   1-column hed.
</P>
<P>
   MISLEADING-MORTGAGES (New York) _ A mortgage lender named Delta
Funding has made a profitable business of loaning money in poor
neighborhoods, where many homeowners can't afford to make their
monthly payments and thus default, losing their homes. Delta is
affiliated with Bankers Trust, and its business has drawn the
attention of law enforcement officials and low-income housing
advocates, who contend that the company is violating federal and
state laws by misleading borrowers and signing homeowners up for
mortgages they cannot afford.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move this story by 8:30 p.m. ET in `a' news file.)
</P>
