<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Monday, Jan. 18, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   INSURANCE-LOOPHOLE (Los Angeles) _ When judges in Glendale,
Calif., fired traffic Commissioner Dona Bracke, they exposed a
loophole that officials say allows hundreds of motorists to escape
the state's mandatory insurance law. By Lee Condon. (Will move in
the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BOX-OFFICE (Los Angeles) _ Teen football drama ``Varsity Blues''
scored at the nation's box office on an NFL playoff weekend,
racking up an estimated $14.3 million. By Dave McNary. (Will move
in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
