<HEADLINE>
TKACHUK MAKES EARLY RETURN TO LINEUP  
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By TIM TYERS  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO _ Coyotes Captain Keith Tkachuk hastened his return to
the ice Sunday night against the Chicago Blackhawks after missing
eight games because of a broken rib.
</P>
<P>
   Plans were for him to return Tuesday night at home vs. St.
Louis.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's tough to sit out, especially when you're the captain,''
said Tkachuk, who wore a protective flak jacket, before Sunday's
game. ``When you don't win, you want to be down there helping and
contributing.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll probably be a little cautious, but when you tell the
coach you want to play and he puts you out there, there are no
excuses. Whether you're 100 percent, 20 percent, 80 percent, you
have to go out and play.''
</P>
<P>
   General Manager Bobby Smith said the decision was made to play
Tkachuk only after it was determined Tkachuk wasn't putting himself
at risk.
</P>
<P>
   The Coyotes' play of late has been ragged, straying from the
strong forechecking and solid neutral zone game they had played
earlier in the season. Entering the Chicago game, they were 9-9-1
in December and January, after a 14-2-2 start and an unbeaten
November. Tkachuk missed 12 of those games because of various
injuries.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's only one guy playing right now, and that's Nikolai
Khabibulin,'' Tkachuk said. ``We're not playing well as a team. We
play one good game and then three bad. We don't have the
consistency we need.
</P>
<P>
   ``In the beginning of the year we did, and played well in every
game. We did the right things. We weren't turning the puck over and
doing the stupid things that make you lose games. We have to get
back to playing solid and just play our game.'' &QL; 
 &QL; 
Crime scene &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Coach Jim Schoenfeld based his decision to start struggling
goalie Jimmy Waite against the Blackhawks partially on trying to
exorcise Waite's slump at the United Center, the very building in
which it started.
</P>
<P>
   After opening the season 6-0-2, Waite has allowed 14 goals in
his past three games. All were losses.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jimmy can win the game,'' Schoenfeld said. ``It's a good
challenge for him. He'd been playing great hockey until our last
game in Chicago (4-3 loss). He had back-to-back performances below
his standards. We think this is the best place to come back and
turn his season around.''
</P>
<P>
   Slap shots &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   With Tkachuk's return, the Coyotes reassigned center Trevor
Litowski to Springfield of the American Hockey League on Sunday
afternoon. Litowski scored his first NHL two games ago in a 5-3 win
over Pittsburgh.
</P>
<P>
   Defenseman Deron Quint was a healthy scratch for the second
straight game since the Coyotes obtained defensive J.J. Daigneault
from Nashville. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
